   At Film Distributor
Mr. Smith said "the company has made great strides forward
from something that was losing money to a firm that has shown
five consecutive quarters of profitability." He said Mr.
Silva was a "small businessman" who realized that "the
business is outgrowing him."
   Mr. Smith, who joined the company 20 months ago, added
that Mr. Silva remains the company's largest shareholder with
a 9% stake. "He sees this move as a benefit to the
shareholder," Mr. Smith said.